"Trainer Training (if they apply during the suspension period). "
"Additionally, they will not be allowed to shadow a current Carpentries "
"Trainer. They may apply or reapply for future rounds of Trainer Training."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:72
msgid "Member Organisation and Local Activities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:73
msgid ""
"The suspended member shall not be involved in officially branded "
"Carpentries workshops or activities at the member or local site for the "
"duration of the suspension. We expect the suspended member to assert that"
" they will be able to carry out this suspension accordingly and to notify"
" the CoC committee if this suspension will interfere with their expected "
"employment duties."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:75
msgid ""
"If the suspension does affect employment duties or the suspended member "
"is the key contact for a member site, the member will work with The "
"Carpentries Executive Director to determine a course of action."
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:77
msgid "Lesson Development and Maintenance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../handbook/topic_folders/policies/termed-suspension.md:78
